/*
To run on Windows:

1. Open Visual Studio.
2. Clone a repository. Fill in Repository Location and Path.
3. Click "Clone".

Chances are, you may need to modify settings to get the program to work. FIRST, do step 1. 
Then, try to build and run the solution (At the top menu, click Build -> Clean Solution. Then click Build -> Rebuild Solution. If no errors, click Local Windows Debugger).
If there are errors, check/modify your settings by doing steps 2 through 5 for each indicated project (bulleted under each step).
Once you do those steps, build and run the solution: Build -> Clean Solution. Then click Build -> Rebuild Solution. Last, click Local Windows Debugger.

1. Right click solution -> Properties -> Common Properties -> Configure Startup Projects -> Multiple startup projects -> Action = Start
- stub_server (if not at top, move to top)
- phase4_controller

2. Right click project -> Properties -> Configuration Properties -> Debugging -> Command Arguments = input dll output temp
- phase4_controller

3. Right click project -> Properties -> Configuration Properties -> General -> Output Directory = $(SolutionDir)bin\
- phase4_controller (main EXE) - makes sure relative paths like input, output, temp work correctly
- mapper_worker
- reducer_worker
- stub_server

4. Right click project -> Properties -> Configuration Properties -> General -> Output Directory = $(SolutionDir)dll\
- mapper_dll
- reducer_dll

5. Right click project -> Properties -> Configuration Properties -> General -> Intermediate Directory = $(SolutionDir)build\$(ProjectName)\
Right click project -> Properties -> Configuration Properties -> Debugging -> Working Directory = $(SolutionDir)
Right click project -> Properties -> Configuration Properties -> C/C++ -> General -> Additional Include Directories = $(SolutionDir)headers
- mapper_dll
- mapper_worker
- phase4_controller
- reducer_dll
- reducer_worker
- stub_server

*/
